OL,3,C100-year-old D-Day veteran awarded
OL,4,CFrance's highest military honour
OL,6,FHe said he was "delighted" to receive
OL,7,Fthe medal and described it as "a great
OL,8,Fhonour indeed."
OL,10,FThe Legion d'Honneur was established
OL,11,Fby Napoleon in 1802. In 2014, the
OL,12,FFrench Government decided to recognise
OL,13,Fall D-Day veterans with the honour in
OL,14,Frecognition of their efforts to
OL,15,Fliberate France in 1944.
