OL,3,C100-year-old D-Day veteran awarded
OL,4,CFrance's highest military honour
OL,6,F"My country was fortunate to be able
OL,7,Fto count on the support of its closest
OL,8,Fpartner, the UK, and of the brave
OL,9,FBritish people who fought for our
OL,10,Fcommon values, freedom, democracy and
OL,11,Fpeace.
OL,13,F"This award ceremony is an opportunity
OL,14,Fto recall the unbreakable friendship
OL,15,Fbetween our two nations.
OL,17,F"Through this award, France wants to
OL,18,Fhonour John Fiddler as the perfect
OL,19,Fexample of an individual who deserves
OL,20,Four endless gratitude."
