OL,3,C100-year-old D-Day veteran awarded
OL,4,CFrance's highest military honour
OL,6,FMr Fiddler said: "Thank you, you're
OL,7,Fall very kind people, thank you very
OL,8,Fmuch."
OL,10,FHis daughter Allyson Fiddler said:
OL,11,F"Like so many of my father's
OL,12,Fgeneration, he, too, would emphasise
OL,13,Fthat he was just doing his duty.
OL,15,F"This is a proud and happy occasion to
OL,16,Freceive this recognition from the
OL,17,FRepublic of France.
